      "writtenOn": "2020-08-12T13:18:04Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I agree. It looks like \u0027rotMatrix\u0027 is limited to rotation and translation. Maybe Michael just thought this was clearer or liked that it fit on one line? There is another arg \u0027viewMatrix\u0027 and \u0027pts\u0027 is clearly on one side of that matrix while \u0027lineData.fPtsRot\u0027 is not. So it does make some logical sense to me even if mathematically it works out the same in the current implementation.",
