        "id": 8341
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-08-31T13:49:09Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "calc_dash_scaling applies the matrix to the points before it calculates the magnitude. It also rotates the vector from pts[0] to pts[1] by 90 CW and then applies the view matrix to get the perpendicular vector. For a view matrix with non-uniform scale factors, you\u0027ll get a different parallel and perpendicular magnitude. When combined with a 90 degree rotation from align_to_x_axis (when dealing with a perfectly vertical line), the old code effectively swapped the x and y non-uniform scale factors.\n\nI agree that it should be just as correct to use rotMatrix with ptsRot, but I thought this was more direct.",
      "parentUuid": "35ad2d66_609349d7",
